                            <comment id="12898236" author="gsingers" created="Fri, 13 Aug 2010 13:45:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Drew.  Fixed on trunk and 3.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12899747" author="ryantxu" created="Wed, 18 Aug 2010 06:01:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since trunk is on java 1.6, we do not any stax dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12899967" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Wed, 18 Aug 2010 19:11:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, good point.  We should investigate at least removing the stax-api.&lt;br/&gt;
We could remove the implementation as well (woodstox) but we should do performance tests before doing so.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mail-archive.com/users@cxf.apache.org/msg12750.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.mail-archive.com/users@cxf.apache.org/msg12750.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12899980" author="ryantxu" created="Wed, 18 Aug 2010 19:42:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;interesting &amp;#8211; i wonder if you have to do anything special to get it to use the different implementation?  is just having it in the classpath enough?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I made an independent ticket for this &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2054&quot; title=&quot;Remove StAX libraries from trunk (java6)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-2054&quot;&gt;SOLR-2054&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13013034" author="gsingers" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2011 15:45:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for 3.1.0 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
